      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(infra): bound jsonl-socket response buffer to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n`requestJsonlSocket` accumulates incoming socket data into a string buffer until a newline is seen or the socket closes. A buggy or hostile peer that streams data without newlines can force the runtime to keep buffering until timeout or OOM.\n\nThis PR bounds that pending JSONL line buffer in the shared requester and adds a matching macOS exec-host producer output budget, so valid command responses are truncated before they can exceed the requester cap.\n\n## Changes\n\n- `src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts`\n  - Adds `JSONL_SOCKET_MAX_BUFFER_BYTES = 16 * 1024 * 1024`.\n  - Returns `null` and destroys the socket once the pending line buffer exceeds the cap.\n  - Exposes the cap through `testApi` so tests stay aligned with the production limit.\n- `src/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts`\n  - Adds a regression test for an oversized newline-free socket response.\n  - Streams chunks over the real socket until the production cap is exceeded and handles the expected server-side EPIPE after the requester destroys the socket.\n  - Asserts the result arrives before the timeout window, so the test proves the cap path instead of the existing timeout path.\n- `apps/macos/Sources/OpenClaw/ExecApprovalsSocket.swift`\n  - Adds `ExecHostOutputLimiter` for macOS exec-host responses.\n  - Caps stdout/stderr fields at 1 MiB each before building the `exec-res` JSONL response.\n- `apps/macos/Tests/OpenClawIPCTests/ExecApprovalsSocketAuthTests.swift`\n  - Adds coverage for small output preservation, oversized output truncation, UTF-8 tail preservation, worst-case escaped JSONL size, and a real command-output response.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior addressed**: A peer streaming a newline-free body larger than the cap must not hang or grow memory until timeout; the call must return `null` quickly.\n- **Real environment tested**: Local Node v22 workspace, real `net.createServer` / `net.Socket` over a Unix domain socket in `/tmp`.\n- **Exact steps**: `node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts` starts a server that streams 64 KiB chunks every 5 ms with no newline, then calls `requestJsonlSocket` with a 2 s timeout.\n- **Observed result after fix**: `RESULT: result=null elapsedMs=104`.\n- **Negative control on current main**: `RESULT: result=null elapsedMs=2016`.\n\n## Current status proof\n\n- **Current head**: `6e4de6fcde9d76cda6e8ddf18d884e8eda4d6934`.\n- **Current GitHub PR diff**: `+131/-5 (4 files)`.\n- **Current changed files**:\n\n```text\napps/macos/Sources/OpenClaw/ExecApprovalsSocket.swift\napps/macos/Tests/OpenClawIPCTests/ExecApprovalsSocketAuthTests.swift\nsrc/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts\nsrc/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n```\n\n## Compatibility proof\n\nThe requester cap is 16 MiB. The macOS exec-host producer now caps stdout and stderr at 1 MiB each before JSON encoding, leaving room for worst-case JSON escaping and response metadata.\n\nWorst-case escaped `exec-res` JSON size probe with both stdout and stderr filled to the 1 MiB field budget with escaped NUL output:\n\n```text\n$ node --input-type=module <<'NODEPROOF'\nconst max = 1024 * 1024;\nconst marker = '... (truncated) ';\nconst escapedNul = String.fromCharCode(92) + 'u0000';\nconst nulTail = escapedNul.repeat(max - Buffer.byteLength(marker));\nconst response = { type: 'exec-res', id: 'test', ok: true, payload: { exitCode: 0, timedOut: false, success: true, stdout: marker + nulTail, stderr: marker + nulTail, error: null }, error: null };\nconst bytes = Buffer.byteLength(JSON.stringify(response));\nconsole.log(JSON.stringify({ bytes, under16MiB: bytes < 16 * 1024 * 1024 }));\nNODEPROOF\n{\"bytes\":14680020,\"under16MiB\":true}\n```\n\nSwift coverage added for the macOS producer:\n\n- small output remains unchanged\n- oversized output is truncated\n- UTF-8 tail is preserved after truncation\n- worst-case escaped `exec-res` stays below the 16 MiB requester cap\n- real `/usr/bin/perl` command output is limited before response encoding\n\nLocal limitation: this Linux checkout does not have Swift or the macOS SDK/AppKit, so `swift test --package-path apps/macos --filter ExecApprovalsSocketAuthTests` cannot run locally (`swift: command not found`). The PR CI `macos-swift` lane is the authoritative Swift proof.\n\n## Evidence\n\nTerminal proof (real socket, streaming peer without newlines):\n\n```text\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts\nRESULT: result=null elapsedMs=104\n```\n\nNegative control (temporary revert to `origin/main`):\n\n```text\n$ git checkout origin/main -- src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n$ node --import tsx /tmp/proof-jsonl-socket.mts\nRESULT: result=null elapsedMs=2016\n$ git checkout HEAD -- src/infra/jsonl-socket.ts\n```\n\nFocused Vitest after adding the pre-timeout cap assertion and macOS producer cap:\n\n```text\n$ node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/jsonl-socket.test.ts --run\n\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  6 passed (6)\n```\n\nThe oversized-buffer regression uses a 500 ms timeout and asserts the result returns in under 250 ms, so current main's timeout-only behavior would not satisfy the test.\n\nWhitespace/check sanity:\n\n```text\n$ git diff --check\n# exit 0\n```\n\nEarlier type checks on this PR:\n\n```text\n$ pnpm tsgo:core      # exit 0\n$ pnpm tsgo:core:test # exit 0\n```\n",
